<plot>When established star Joan Crawford was paired in a film with earthy newcomer Clark Gable, a torrid extramarital affair ensued which translated into a tempestuous relationship that threatened to burn down Hollywood. But, the threat of a scandal had studio chief L.B. Mayer forbid the affair, which finally mellowed into an intimate friendship that would endure three marriages and the death of Carole Lombard.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?208276</url></doc>
